  "prompt": "What are the new features in iPhone 7?",
  "response": "The iPhone 7, released in September 2016, introduced several new features:\n\n1. Water and dust resistance (IP67 rating)\n\n2. Removed 3.5mm headphone jack, replaced with Lightning port for audio\n\n3. Stereo speakers\n\n4. Dual-lens camera on iPhone 7 Plus (with optical zoom and portrait mode)\n\n5. Improved single-lens camera on iPhone 7\n\n6. A10 Fusion chip with improved performance\n\n7. Longer battery life compared to previous models\n\n8. New color options, including Jet Black and matte Black\n\n9. Home button redesigned with haptic feedback (taptic engine)\n\n10. 256GB storage option (in addition to 32GB and 128GB)\n\nThese features were significant updates to the iPhone line at the time, particularly the water resistance, camera improvements, and removal of the headphone jack.",
